The paper deals with game theory and its application to concurrent and multi-agent systems, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on Nash equilibrium, which is a central concept in game theory, making the category of Game Theory (cs.GT) another likely choice. The paper also discusses the modelling of strategies, which could place it in the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of temporal logic in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the preservation of properties under bisimilarity, which is a topic in Software Engineering (cs.SE).
